href=3D"https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~amp12/" =
class=3D"">https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~amp12/</a>)</div><div class=3D"">- =
Simona Ronchi della Rocca</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; (<a =
href=3D"http://www.di.unito.it/~ronchi/" =
class=3D"">http://www.di.unito.it/~ronchi/</a>) &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">FSCD (<a =
href=3D"http://fscdconference.org/" =
class=3D"">http://fscdconference.org/</a>&nbsp;) covers all aspects of =
formal structures for computation&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">and =
deduction from theoretical foundations to applications. Building on two =
communities, RTA</div><div class=3D"">(Rewriting Techniques and =
Applications) and TLCA (Typed Lambda Calculi and =
Applications),&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">FSCD embraces their core =
topics and broadens their scope to closely related areas in =
logics,&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">models of computation, semantics and =
verification in new challenging areas.&nbsp;</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">The suggested, but not exclusive, list =
of topics for submission is:</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">1.&nbsp;Calculi:&nbsp;Rewriting systems =
(string, term, higher-order, graph,&nbsp;conditional, modulo, =
infinitary, etc.);</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Lambda calculus; =
Logics&nbsp;(first-order, higher-order, equational, modal, linear, =
classical,&nbsp;constructive, etc.);&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; =
&nbsp; Proof&nbsp;theory (natural deduction, sequent&nbsp;calculus, =
proof nets, etc.); Type theory and logical frameworks;&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Homotopy type theory; Quantum =
calculi.</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D"">2.&nbsp;Methods in =
Computation and Deduction:&nbsp;Type systems (poly-&nbsp;morphism, =
dependent, recursive, intersection, session, etc.);&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Induction, coinduction; Matching, unification, =
completion, order-&nbsp;ings; Strategies&nbsp;(normalization, =
completeness, etc.);&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Tree =
automata; Model building and model checking; Proof search =
and&nbsp;theorem proving;&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; =
Constraint solving and decision procedures.<br class=3D""><br =
class=3D"">3.&nbsp;Semantics:&nbsp;Operational semantics and abstract =
machines;&nbsp;Game Semantics and applications;&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Domain theory and categorical models; =
Quantitative models (timing, probabilities, etc.);&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Quantum computation and&nbsp;emerging models in =
computation.<br class=3D""><br class=3D"">4.&nbsp;Algorithmic Analysis =
and Transformations of Formal Systems:&nbsp;Type Inference and type =
checking;&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Abstract =
Interpretation;&nbsp;Complexity analysis and implicit computational =
complexity;&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Checking =
termination,&nbsp;confluence, derivational complexity and&nbsp;related =
properties; Symbolic computation.<br class=3D""><br =
class=3D"">5.&nbsp;Tools and Applications:&nbsp;Programming and proof =
environments;&nbsp;Verification tools;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; =
&nbsp; Proof assistants and interactive theorem&nbsp;provers; =
Applications in industry;&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; =
Applications of formal sys-&nbsp;tems in other sciences.<br class=3D""><br=
 class=3D"">6.&nbsp;Semantics and Verification in new challenging =
areas:&nbsp;Certification; Security; Blockchain =
protocols;&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">&nbsp; &nbsp; Data Bases; Deep =
learning&nbsp;and machine learning algorithms; Planning.</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">PUBLICATION</div><div =
class=3D"">--------------------</div><div class=3D"">The proceedings =
will be published as an electronic volume in the Leibniz =
International</div><div class=3D"">Proceedings in Informatics (LIPIcs) =
of Schloss Dagstuhl. All LIPIcs proceedings are open access.</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">SPECIAL ISSUE</div><div =
class=3D"">----------------------</div><div class=3D"">Authors of =
selected papers will be invited to submit an extended version to a =
special issue of&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">Logical Methods in Computer =
Science.</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D""><b =
class=3D"">SUBMISSION GUIDELINES</b>&nbsp;</div><div =
class=3D"">--------------------------------------</div><div =
class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" class=3D"">Submissions can be made in =
two categories. Regular research papers are limited to 15 =
pages,&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">excluding references. They must present original research =
which is unpublished and not&nbsp;submitted =
elsewhere.&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">Proofs and other&nbsp;technical details that do not fit =
within the page limit can be submitted as an appendix (up to 5 =
pages).&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">The appendix will be&nbsp;consulted at the discretion of the =
reviewers.&nbsp;Therefore, submissions must be self-contained =
within&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">the respective page limit; the&nbsp;additional material =
should not be necessary to assess the merits of a =
submission.&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">System descriptions are limited to 15 pages,&nbsp;excluding =
references. They must present new software tools,&nbsp;</font></div><div =
class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" class=3D"">or significantly new =
versions of such tools, in which FSCD topics&nbsp;play an important =
role. An archive of the code&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font =
color=3D"#b92d5d" class=3D"">with instructions on how to install =
and&nbsp;run the tool must be submitted. In&nbsp;addition, a webpage =
where the system can be&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font =
color=3D"#b92d5d" class=3D"">experimented with should be =
provided.&nbsp;</font></div><div class=3D""><font color=3D"#b92d5d" =
class=3D"">Complete instructions on submitting a&nbsp;paper can be found =
on the conference web site.</font></div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">BEST PAPER AWARD BY JUNIOR =
RESEARCHERS</div><div =
class=3D"">--------------------------------------</div><div class=3D"">The=
 program committee will select a paper in which at least one author is a =
junior researcher,&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">i.e. either a student or =
whose PhD award date is less than three years from the first day of the =
meeting.&nbsp;</div><div class=3D"">Other authors should declare to the =
PC Chair that at least 50% of contribution is made by the junior =
researcher(s).</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div =
